        <p class="metadata">Posted by Shahar Evron (shahar) on 2007-08-20T10:30:06.000+0000</p> 
        <div class="body">
            <p>I Disagree.</p>

<p>The reason is that a Zend_Http_Response object is not instantiated (and should not be)  if there is no <em>HTTP</em> response.</p>

<p>Since there is no connection, there is no HTTP request and no HTTP response, so there cannot be a call to $response-&gt;isSuccessful() method.</p>

<p>$response-&gt;isSuccessful() / -&gt;isError() etc. relate to the <em>HTTP</em> response code, not to some networking or other related issues.</p>

<p>You should (and can, very easily) use try / catch in your code to make sure there are no networking issues.</p>

<p>If you think this should be further discussed, please submit to fw-webserives@lists.zend.com and take the discussion there, so everyone can participate.</p>

<p>I am closing this bug for now.</p>

